# Natural Earth data is in WGS84 (EPSG:4326); for distance calculations, we use a projected CRS.
# Here we use World Mercator (EPSG:3395) to measure distances in meters.
world_proj    <- st_transform(world, 3395)
pa_points_proj <- st_transform(pa_points, 3395)

1.3: Histogram of Average Distance to Ports/Airports by Country

Histogram of Average Distance to Ports/Airports by Country: Calculates the average distance (in kilometers) from each countrys centroid to the ports/airports within its boundaries, displayed by continent.

# Calculate, for each country, the average distance (in km) from its centroid to the ports/airports within its boundaries.

avg_distance_list <- lapply(seq_len(nrow(world_proj)), function(i) {
  # Safely extract attributes; if absent, assign NA_character_
  country_iso       <- if (length(world_proj$iso_a3[i]) == 0) NA_character_ else as.character(world_proj$iso_a3[i])
  country_name      <- if (length(world_proj$NAME[i]) == 0) NA_character_ else as.character(world_proj$NAME[i])
  country_continent <- if (length(world_proj$CONTINENT[i]) == 0) NA_character_ else as.character(world_proj$CONTINENT[i])
  
  # Extract the country's polygon
  country_poly <- world_proj[i, ]
  
  # Check if the country's geometry is empty
  if (st_is_empty(country_poly)) {
    return(data.frame(
      iso_a3 = country_iso,
      country = country_name,
      continent = country_continent,
      avg_distance = NA_real_,
      stringsAsFactors = FALSE
    ))
  }
  
  # Select points that fall within the country's polygon
  in_country_logical <- st_within(pa_points_proj, country_poly, sparse = FALSE)[, 1]
  pa_in_country <- pa_points_proj[in_country_logical, ]
  
  if (nrow(pa_in_country) > 0) {
    # Calculate the country's centroid
    centroid <- st_centroid(country_poly)
    # If the centroid is empty, assign NA
    if (st_is_empty(centroid)) {
      avg_dist <- NA_real_
    } else {
      distances <- st_distance(centroid, pa_in_country)
      avg_dist  <- mean(as.numeric(distances)) / 1000  # Convert to kilometers
    }
  } else {
    avg_dist <- NA_real_  # No points found within the country
  }
  
  data.frame(
    iso_a3 = country_iso,
    country = country_name,
    continent = country_continent,
    avg_distance = avg_dist,
    stringsAsFactors = FALSE
  )
})

# Combine the list into a single data frame
avg_distance_df <- do.call(rbind, avg_distance_list)

# Filter countries that have a calculated distance (exclude those with no points)
avg_distance_df_clean <- avg_distance_df %>% filter(!is.na(avg_distance))

# Create a histogram, faceted by continent
hist_distance <- ggplot(avg_distance_df_clean, aes(x = avg_distance)) +
  geom_histogram(fill = "steelblue", bins = 30, color = "black", alpha = 0.7) +
  facet_wrap(~ continent) +
  labs(
    title = "Histogram of Average Distance to Ports/Airports by Country",
    x = "Average Distance (km)",
    y = "Number of Countries"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

# Display the histogram
print(hist_distance)

coast_distance <- st_distance(markets, coastline_africa, by_element = FALSE)
coast_min_distances <- apply(X = coast_distance, MARGIN = 1, FUN = min, na.rm = TRUE)
markets$coast_min_distances_km <- coast_min_distances / 1000

closest_coast_indices <- apply(coast_distance, 1, which.min)

# Scatter plot for average coast

market_prices <- readxl::read_excel(file.path(path_data,  "1.-Price--Production--and-Population-Data/PriceMaster4GAMS.xlsx"))

# Average price by market id

# Convert price columns to numeric
price_cols <- as.character(1:144)  # Columns "1" to "144"
market_prices[price_cols] <- lapply(market_prices[price_cols], as.numeric)

# Compute average price per mktcode, excluding 0 and NA values
avg_prices <- market_prices %>%
  rowwise() %>%
  mutate(avg_price = mean(c_across(all_of(price_cols))[c_across(all_of(price_cols)) > 0], na.rm = TRUE)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(mktcode) %>%
  summarise(avg_price = mean(avg_price, na.rm = TRUE))
